Detailed Description

The interface for handling key and pointer events.

Member Function Documentation

bool WFAPI::MapLibKeyInterface::handleKeyEvent ( keyType  key,
kindOfPressType  type 
)

Handles the press of a key. If the type of event is KEY_DOWN_EVENT, the map will move in an accelerating manner until the same key is sent with a KEY_UP_EVENT.

Parameters:
key The key which was pressed.
type Type of event.
Returns:
True if the key was consumed.

bool WFAPI::MapLibKeyInterface::handlePointerEvent ( pointerType  key,
kindOfPointerType  type,
const WFAPI::ScreenPoint &  dragToPoint 
)

Handles the press of a key. If the type of event is KEY_DOWN_EVENT, the map will move in an accelerating manner until the same key is sent with a KEY_UP_EVENT. Use this method when supplying a DRAG_TO key event.

Parameters:
key The key which was pressed.
type Type of event.
dragToPoint Contains the current position of the pointer device.
Returns:
True if the key was consumed.

void WFAPI::MapLibKeyInterface::stop (  ) 

Stops the current action (i.e. in case KEY_UP_EVENT has not been received yet).
